The other end of the optomechanical coupling is given by the field-to-force TF. It stems from the radiation pressure (RP) that light exerts on the mirrors. Thus the TF in question is a vector of coefficients at the corresponding quadratures of the input fields in the expression for a back-action force, FBA\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
