The original paper by Braginsky and Khalili (1990) considered the microwave speed meter as a readout for bar GW detectors. The first of two proposed schemes was the microwave version of the scheme shown in Fig. 17. The second one used two coupled microwave cavities with one of them having a movable wall attached to the bar antenna to sense the GW-induced oscillations thereof, and the other cavity served for storing the EM signal with displacement information and sending (“sloshing”) it back to the readout cavity with an opposite sign (π\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
