The left panel shows the general scheme for the white-light-cavity cavity, where a negative-dispersion (ND) element is placed inside the signal-recycling cavity. The internal signal-recycling mirror (iSRM), which has the same transmission as ITM, is introduced to form an impedance match cavity with ITM so that the signal sidebands are not affected by the narrow bandwidth of the arm cavity. The right panel shows a realisation using the unstable optomechanical filter. A global feedback control is needed to stabilise the system

